-----BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----

[PGP PUBLIC KEY PLACEHOLDER]

This file should contain the actual PGP public key for the StellarSwipe
security team. The key should be generated and added before the security
vulnerability disclosure program goes live.

To generate a PGP key pair:

1. Install GPG:
   - macOS: brew install gnupg
   - Linux: apt-get install gnupg (or equivalent)
   - Windows: Download from https://gpg4win.org

2. Generate key:
   gpg --full-generate-key
   
   Recommended settings:
   - Key type: RSA and RSA
   - Key size: 4096 bits
   - Expiration: 2 years (renewable)
   - Real name: StellarSwipe Security Team
   - Email: security@stellarswipe.io

3. Export public key:
   gpg --armor --export security@stellarswipe.io > pgp-key.asc

4. Publish key:
   - Replace this file with the exported key
   - Upload to key servers:
     gpg --send-keys KEY_ID
   - Publish fingerprint in SECURITY.md

Key Management Best Practices:
- Store private key securely (hardware security key recommended)
- Use strong passphrase
- Keep backup of private key in secure location
- Set expiration and renew regularly
- Revoke if compromised

Key Fingerprint: [TO BE ADDED]

For encrypted communication with the security team:
1. Import this key: gpg --import pgp-key.asc
2. Encrypt your message: gpg --encrypt --armor -r security@stellarswipe.io message.txt
3. Send encrypted message to: security@stellarswipe.io

Alternative secure channels:
- Keybase: stellarswipe_security
- Signal: [TO BE ADDED]
- GitHub Security Advisory (private)

